Results.Title: TEST VPN Upgrade
Results.Description: Hello, Infor has a requirement to quickly upgrade all customer facing VPN devices. As such, we will be scheduling your NONPROD VPN upgrades for the below date: Date: May 24th 2018 Time: Between 6PM and 2AM local time Environments: Enter Affected Environments Why is this upgrade necessary? • Infor has been working closely with our VPN device vendor, Cohesive Networks, to make improvements to the VPN devices. The result is that the new 4.3 version of the VPN device has been released with many underlying stability improvements, enhanced networking, better logging, and additional monitoring capabilities. • The latest version includes REQUIRED Meltdown / Spectre mitigation patching • This is required to enable VPN As A Service in the Cloudsuite Self Service portal What do we (the customer) need to change on our side? Our engineers will be reviewing our monitoring and logs for your Infor VPN devices prior to the upgrade. If all of the settings appear to match up correctly and no issues are noted in the logs, nothing needs to change for you. If we do discover potential issues, we will detail those issues in an IXS ticket and work with your Network Engineer to resolve. Do we (the customer) need to take any action when the upgrade is made? Yes. Once the upgrade is complete on the Infor side, we will update the IXS ticket that our work is complete. Before using the VPN, we ask that the customer Network Engineer restart the tunnel on the customer side to get a clean connection with the new VPN device and verify that traffic is flowing as expected. How long will the upgrade take? We are asking for 1 hour per environment (1 hour for prod, 1 hour for dev, etc). This allows us to make the upgrade and verify settings and logs before closing the maintenance window. If there were settings that needed to be investigated/changed, we may ask for 2 hours for that environment. What is the risk of doing the upgrade? The risk is very low. We are replacing, not upgrading, the existing VPN device. The old (currently working) device will still be available. If for any reason the newly upgraded device cannot successfully establish the VPN connection, we will roll back to the previous device. At that point, the VPN will be established as it was before and Infor will investigate why the upgrade was not successful, then reschedule the upgrade again for a future date. What are the next steps? An IXS ticket will be opened (if one has not been already) to track the upgrade. If an IXS has already been created and downtime scheduled for Windows OS Patching, the upgrade will be included in that window. An Infor Engineer will update the IXS with details regarding the device that will be upgraded and any recommended changes to the settings to improve stability. Once a time for the upgrade is agreed upon, we will use the IXS to track the progress of the upgrade. Technical Info / Links: If you are running one of following devices, please review the documentation to make sure that your devices are configured using the recommended settings. Cisco ASA: https://cohesive.net/dnld/Cohesive-Networks_Cisco-ASDM-9.2-IPsec-Setup.pdf Juniper: https://cohesive.net/dnld/Cohesive-Networks_Juniper-SSG-IPsec-Setup.pdf Sonicwall: https://cohesive.net/dnld/Cohesive-Networks_SonicWall-NSA-240-IPsec-Setup.pdf FortiOS: https://cohesive.net/dnld/Cohesive-Networks_FortiOS-541-IPsec-Setup.pdf
Results.Resolution: Customer is using Direct Connect - AWS DX
